missionEventData.data2: In the far reaches of the Outer Rim a rebellion is forming. A rebel cell led by the frigate Redemption and ace pilot Keyan Farlander have been striking back against the evil galactic empire. But the Emperor is at the height of his power, and even now he is marshalling his forces at the edge of the mid-rim. But help has come from the most unlikely of places. The captain of an imperial corvette has sent the rebel freedom fighters a secret message, he wishes to defect...

missionEventData.data1: The Astromech units that were being carried by the Ars Opus were imperial units! They hijacked a squadron of our X-Wing fighters and jumped out of the system. Weâ€™ve tracked three of the ships to an adjoining system. In your Y-Wing use your ion cannons to knock out their systems. The Bixby will then jump in to collect them. Expect interference. Imperial Intelligence have clearly been planning this operation for a long time!
The X-Wings have already jumped. Get after them immediately!
Okay Red Squadron, there they are, activate your targeting computers and switch to ion cannons. Remember we're here to disable them, not destroy them.
This is the Bixby. We're going to collect those X-Wings. Protect us from any imperial Interference.
This is the Bixby. Gold One has been reacquired.
A ship is jumping in. It's the Warspite. They're launching bombers. Keep them off the Bixby until they can jump.
Another group of bombers are launching. Intercept them!
All Tie Bombers have been destroyed.
We're preparing to exit the system. Keep us covered while we jump to hyperspace.
Acknowledged Bixby. We've got you covered.
Well done Red Squadron. Get to the jump point and we're done.
Acknowledged Redemption. Already on our way out.
They're launching fighters. Looks like they want to clear us out before they take another run at the Bixby.
We need to clear out all the fighters before we can safely make the jump.

missionEventData.data3: The betrayal of the Ars Opus is a grievous blow but thanks to your rapid response we were able to recover three of our X-Wing ships. Although the chances are slim we will be on the lookout to see if we can rescue the rest of our lost pilotsâ€¦
